  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n^2.18.1\n\n### What happened?\n\nI am forking mumbai, using `hardhat node` and fork config, to run tests and I randomly get this error:\r\n\r\n`ProviderError: missing trie node cd415b780637a9866aa655a8e23ff7b2e2695086783c91e7a8fc00020bc43544 (path ) <nil>`\r\n\r\nAccording to this: https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/149254/using-hardhat-to-fork-a-node-but-getting-missing-trie-node/155695?noredirect=1#comment172491_155695 , it could be caused by the fork being outdated after a while. \r\n\r\nHow do I avoid this? \n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\n1. Fork mumbai with hardhat node and \r\nhardhat: {\r\n      forking: {\r\n        url: `${process.env.ALCHEMY_MUMBAI_URL}`,\r\n      },\r\n    },\r\n2. Run tests at least 5/10mn after the node was started\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
